Kenya’s Crown Berger, Flowcrete Sign Manufacturing Agreement

-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 
2011-05-10T08:11:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-10/kenya-s-crown-berger-flowcrete-sign-manufacturing-agreement.html
Crown Berger  Kenya  Ltd. and  Flowcrete
South Africa  signed an agreement in which the Kenyan company
will manufacture resin floors.  The partnership includes making floor products and training
Crown Berger staff, Rakesh Rao, managing director of Kenya’s
only publicly traded paint-maker, told reporters in Nairobi
today.  “This initial partnership commits both companies for five
years and will see Crown Berger cover Kenya, Uganda, Rwanda,
Sudan, Tanzania and Burundi on behalf of Flowcrete,” Rao said.  Flowcrete  South Africa  is a unit of U.K.-based Flowcrete
Group Plc., which is owned by RPM International Inc. of America.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at 
 eombok@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net 
